From: halildeu <halildeu@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 13:15:26 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(context-faz3-4): canonical store + multi-agent
 coordination + SDK
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Faz 3 — CP-5: Canonical Decision Store
- canonical_store.py: promoted permanent decisions with temporal lifecycle
- fact ≠ decision separation (separate stores)
- promote_decision(): ephemeral → canonical (auto or approved)
- promote_from_ephemeral(): batch promote above confidence threshold
- query(): glob pattern + category filter + expiration check
- Temporal fields: fresh_until, review_after, expires_at, supersedes
- Provenance tracking: evidence_id linkage

Faz 4 — CP-6: Multi-Agent Coordination + SDK Hooks
- agent_coordination.py: revision-based stale detection
- get_revision(): SHA256 hash of canonical store
- check_stale(): detect if another agent modified store
- read_with_revision(): read with revision metadata

SDK Hooks:
- record_decision(): write + auto-promote if confident
- compile_context_sdk(): canonical + facts + session → compiled preamble
- finalize_session_sdk(): compact + distill + promote
- query_memory(): query canonical decisions + facts

Multi-agent scenario test: Agent A writes → Agent B reads → Agent A
writes again → Agent B detects stale → Agent B refreshes ✅

32 new tests, 364 total passing.

